and then start complaining.

00:26:19.611 --> 00:26:22.514 line:95%,end
I said, buy seven of the same thing.

00:26:22.581 --> 00:26:25.417 line:95%,end
You know what, I'm getting sick and tired
about hearing these snoods, okay?

00:26:25.483 --> 00:26:28.853 line:95%,end
ABBY: I want the thin ones
that Holly bought

00:26:28.920 --> 00:26:32.190 line:95%,end
in everybody's hair,
and I want this in Nia's hair.

00:26:32.257 --> 00:26:34.225 line:95%,end
We have to have the same thing.

00:26:34.292 --> 00:26:35.493 line:95%,end
I'm the choreographer.

00:26:35.560 --> 00:26:37.128 line:95%,end
Yoo-hoo, I'm over here.

00:26:37.195 --> 00:26:38.630 line:95%,end
<i>I designed the costume.</i>

00:26:38.930 --> 00:26:41.933 line:95%,end
The rats and the snoods make the number.

00:26:44.703 --> 00:26:45.937 line:95%,end
What do you mean last night?

00:26:47.172 --> 00:26:48.006 line:95%,end
MELISSA: We had a soiree--

00:26:48.073 --> 00:26:51.042 line:95%,end
We had a soiree,
and she was the only person there.

00:26:51.109 --> 00:26:52.777 line:95%,end
Wait a minute, wait a minute,
wait a minute.

00:26:53.244 --> 00:26:56.381 line:95%,end
When I left last night,
you all didn't go up to your rooms?

00:26:56.448 --> 00:26:58.383 line:95%,end
JILL: No, we went and changed.

00:26:59.517 --> 00:27:01.820 line:95%,end
Well, I think that's
really going behind my back,

00:27:01.886 --> 00:27:02.821 line:95%,end
and I don't appreciate it.

00:27:02.887 --> 00:27:03.955 line:95%,end
But what does she have to say?

00:27:04.022 --> 00:27:05.557 line:95%,end
Because that's solicitation.

00:27:05.824 --> 00:27:08.293 line:95%,end
